<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 8:14PM CDT  by NWS Hastings</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Nance, northern
Merrick, southern Sherman and Howard Counties through 900 PM CDT...
At 812 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Genoa to near Litchfield. Movement was
east southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Genoa, Farwell, Saint Paul, and Fullerton
Other locations in the path of these storms include Rockville and
Dannebrog.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
